        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI tested in sandbox (with tweaked docker login script) a new multi-arch job [1] (which passes docker login) and a regular job that doesn't use docker [2] (which doesn't try to do docker login). \n\nLet me know if you prefer that I do a copy of the '{project-name}-{stream}-merge-java' altogether.\n\nAlso please note that I had to call the login script directly. When I used lf-infra-docker-login as a step in the conditional builder, only its last builder (lf-provide-maven-settings-cleanup) was included.\n\n[1] https://jenkins.onap.org/sandbox/job/policy-docker-amd64-master-merge-java/1/console\n[2] https://jenkins.onap.org/sandbox/job/aai-champ-master-merge-java/2/console",
        "patchset_number": 1
